<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 09 at 6:03PM CST  by NWS Houston - Galveston</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT SOUTH CENTRAL FORT BEND COUNTY
THROUGH 645 PM CST...
At 602 PM CST, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Needville, or 8 miles southwest of Rosenberg, moving east at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Southern Rosenberg, Needville, Pleak, Fairchilds, Beasley, Thompsons,
Brazos Bend State Park, southern Riverstone, and Greatwood.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
